 In FY 2026, AF DCGS will transition from four ACAT III efforts (GEOINT Transformation, SIGINT Transformation, Multi-INT Infrastructure, and Network Infrastructure
 Transformation) to one Software Acquisition Pathway (SWP), encompassing Mission Applications, Mission Data Services, and DCGS Operations Integration and
 Transformation (OI&T), and maintain the Network Infrastructure Transformation (NIT) ACAT III. The SWP with its realigned categories will consist of the efforts formerly
 in the GEOINT Transformation, SIGINT Transformation and Multi-INT Infrastructure ACATs. Adopting SWP will improve responsiveness to warfighter needs for
 software-centric capabilities, expedite minimum viable products, drive technology integration, and align agile release trains with streamlined acquisition.

