FY 2026 Plans:
- Continue to develop tools and algorithms for Cyber-EW (Electronic Warfare) capabilities for tactical
engagement.
- Continue research to identify cyber threats (cyber health assessments) including vulnerability research of
ubiquitous embedded systems focusing on devices commonly carried by Marines
- Continue research of low Size, Weight and Power (SWAP) cyber secure technologies that when integrated
into a single platform will enable dismounted Marines to conduct Cyber-EW missions in a highly responsive,
dynamically reprogrammable and modular standards-based configuration.
- Continue research development of distributed mission planning with multi-security enclaves on tactical Cyber-
EW systems.

