       Change Summary Explanation
       The decrease from FY 2026 to FY 2027 is primarily attributed to the shift from the Production and Deployment phase to the Operations & Sustainment phase of
       the Systems Development Lifecycle. The design and development, test and evaluation, and product support efforts for the ACV Family of Vehicles completed in
       FY 2026; funding in FY 2027 provides integration and evaluation of capability-based improvements designed to meet emerging threats and to address component
       improvements related to sustainment, obsolescence, or minor technology updates. Specifically, funding in FY 2027 provides integration and evaluation of the
       Active Protective System (APS), Common Remotely Operated Weapon System (CROWS) Javelin (CROWS-J), Programmable Airburst Munition (PABM), kinetic
       and non-kinetic Counter-small Unmanned Aerial Systems (C-sUAS), the completion of Logistics Demonstration for ACV-R, and completion of the design and
       development of the Crew Gunnery Trainer (CGT).




