FY 2026 Plans:
-Continue Rapid Neutralization of Mines and Obstacles effort in rapid neutralization of mines and obstacles
including development of lethality and vulnerability models, technology concept assessments, and approaches
for neutralization of mines and obstacles in all water depths, the surf zone, beach and inland. The objective is to
enable maneuver of joint forces from ship to inland objective.

-Continue Advanced Minesweeping effort including development of compact, efficient approaches for sweeping
advanced influence mines. The objective is to increase the safe standoff of various tactical platforms and surface
ships.

-Continue Robotics development of robotic technologies to respond to detected targets including work on
dexterity, haptics, and algorithms to achieve human-like behaviors. The objective is to interact with the mine and/
or obstacle to achieve target neutralization, clearance, render-safe or removal for exploitation.

-Initiate Advanced Energetics effort in development of advanced formulations to harness and be tailored for
the undersea environment. Initiate development in integration and tailoring of advanced energetic payloads
to various autonomous systems and platforms, to include enabling capabilities like Size, Weight and Power
(SWaP) requirements, and communications capabilities. The objective is an enduring applied research
investment in undersea lethality and its enabling research thrusts as applied to the seabed environment, as well
as those systems operating in the volume.
