Title: Composites Processing and Fabrication                                                                        8.000  16.748         16.221   0.000  16.221
                                                                                                       Articles:       -       -              -       -        -
Description: The primary technical goal of the Composites Processing and Fabrication activity is improving
weapon systems throughput, affordability, and/or capability enhancements through the increased utilization of
composite and other non-metallic materials and structures. This is being achieved through the development,
maturation, and transition of affordable and robust manufacturing, assembly, and repair processes that fully
exploit the benefits of composite and other non-metallic materials. Concentration is on: VIRGINIA Class
submarine (VCS)/COLUMBIA Class submarine (CLB), DDG 51 Class destroyer, CVN 78 Class carrier, F-35
Lightning II aircraft, and PEO IWS systems.

Composites processing and fabrication technology area includes the development of new and improved
manufacturing processes for materials systems technology including but not limited to fiber-reinforced polymeric
(organic) resin composites; ceramic-matrix, metal-matrix, and carbon-carbon composites; materials for
radomes and other electrical applications; polymer additive materials; insulation materials; coatings; and
adhesives. Manufacturing process areas include but are not limited to forming, machining, bonding and related
technologies, additive manufacturing, and non-destructive inspection. Emphasis is placed on developing
automated and robotic processes for the above.

For FY27, the energetics manufacturing technology portfolio is moving from the Manufacturing Enterprise/Other
activity to the Composites Processing and Fabrication activity. Focus is on energetics process development and
optimization, modeling and simulation, engineering, production, test and evaluation, fleet/operations support.
Energetic manufacturing priorities include identification of weapons system and manufacturing base need and
development, demonstration, and transition of energetics manufacturing technologies.

FY 2026 Plans:
- Complete composites efforts in support of key platforms in technology areas including machining of carbon-
carbon composites and in adhesive bonding.



