Description: The primary technical goal of the Electronics Processing and Fabrication activity is improving
electronic weapon systems affordability by developing and transitioning affordable, robust manufacturing
processes and capabilities for electronics critical to defense applications over their full life-cycle. Efforts
create new and improved electronics/electro-optics manufacturing processes for transition to the production
floor. Emphasis is on VIRGINIA Class submarine (VCS)/COLUMBIA Class submarine (CLB), DDG 51 Class
destroyer, CVN 78 Class carrier, F-35 Lightning II aircraft, and PEO IWS systems.

Electronics processing and fabrication technology areas include, but are not limited to: compound
semiconductors/wide bandgap semiconductors; low-cost, high-throughput manufacturing and assembly
techniques; nanoelectronics; electronics packaging technologies (including tamper proof and non-hermetic
approaches); optics manufacturing technology (materials devices, circuits, modules, subsystems); optical
interconnects; fiber optics and photonics; technologies for electronics and electro-optics testing and evaluation;
optical imaging for manufacturing operations; and High Energy Laser (HEL)/directed energy weapons.

FY 2026 Plans:
- Complete electronics / electro-optics projects in support of key platforms in technology areas such as
focal plane array photonics, inspection technologies, advanced ceramics, electronic connectors, and sonar
transformer manufacturing.
- Continue to develop and transition electronics and electro-optics manufacturing technology improvements that
result in expanded through-put, affordability, and enhanced capability for key platforms: VCS/CLB, DDG 51,
CVN 78, F-35, and PEO IWS systems.
- Continue electronics / electro-optics projects in support of key platforms in technology areas such as focal
plane array photonics, undersea ceramics, and inspection technologies.
- Initiate electronics / electro-optics projects in support of key platforms in technology areas such as inspection
technologies, electronic assembly automation, and sensor manufacturing.
FY 2027 Base Plans:
- Complete electronics / electro-optics projects in support of key platforms in technology areas such as focal
plane array photonics, inspection technologies, sensor manufacturing, and sonar transformer manufacturing.
- Continue to develop and transition electronics and electro-optics manufacturing technology improvements
that result in expanded through-put, affordability, and enhanced capability primarily for PEO IWS systems and
additional key platforms: VCS/CLB, DDG 51, CVN 78, and F-35.


