1319: Research, Development, Test & Evaluation, Navy / BA 4: Advanced     PE 0603563N / Ship Concept Advanced Design
Component Development & Prototypes (ACD&P)
       Project 3161 NAVSEA Tech Authority: Decrease due to Additive Manufacturing and Learn to Action Board efforts moving to other program elements to improve
       transparency.

       Project 3244 Cybersecurity Engineering: In FY 2027, Situational Awareness Boundary Enforcement and Response (SABER) is a Program of Record and
       transitioned to NAVWAR PEO C4I/PMW130 PE: 0303140N / Project: 3244 per ASN(RDA) direction. NAVSEA Red Team is a ZERO SUM realignment of funds
       within NAVSEA accounts to PE 0603563N Project 3244 to support the operation of the NAVSEA Red Team per OPNAV direction. The program provides the
       capability to research, identify, validate, and execute missions to determine nation-state exploitable (Tier IV) cyber vulnerabilities in deployed and next-generation
       warfighting platforms and weapons.

       Project 3376 Strategic Sealift: Increased funds the completion of the modification of 5 T-AKEs to enable them to conduct VLS rearm at anchor up to sea state 3.
       This includes replacing the aft crane with a commercial-based motion compensating crane and finishing work to reposition the aft crane to port side forward to
       support in-port Mk48 torpedo reload on the 5 T-AKEs. Additionally, the funding will be used for installation and demonstration of ASRV technologies on the USNS
       MONTFORD POINT (T-ESD 1) and will provide a cost-effective Vertical Launch System (VLS) rearm at-sea solution that will be fully compatible with all CRUDES
       and Allied/Partner Mk41 equipped vessels.

       Project 3505 Maritime Prepositioning Force Next: Increased due to requirements development, program management support, concept engineering to support
       multiple AoAs, major vessel conversion technical package development, multiple vessel specification development, multiple industry study contracts, and new
       construction management contracts. Overall, this budget increase reflects accountability of conducting three concurrent future sealift projects: Crane Ship (T-
       ACS(X)), Maritime Prepositioning Ship (MPS(X)) and Aviation Maintenance Ship (T-AVB(X)) recapitalizations efforts..

       Project 4045 Next Generation Medium Logistics Ship (NGLS): Decreased by 1.124M between FY2026 and FY2027 is due to Lead Hull procurement shifting the
       right.

       Project 5010 AS(X) Submarine Tender: Increased funds in FY2027 reflects acceleration of procurement of both lead and follow ship DD&C shifting left to FY2027.
       Additional RDT&E,N is required to continue design maturation efforts to improve design definition/maturity, cost certainty, & affordability including interfacing with
       industry to integrate Vendor Furnished Information (VFI) into the design. Additional funding required to complete acquisition documentation to conduct Milestone
       B/C, revise, release, & award DD&C RFP for both ships as well as further test planning.




