       Change Summary Explanation
       The FY 2026 request for SPY-6 Family of Radars includes $74,937K of discretionary and $13,000K of mandatory (reconciliation) for a total of $87,937K. The
       mandatory funds partially fund the development of signal processing algorithms and techniques for the SPY-6 Radar to improve electronic protection capabilities.
       Further information for this reconciliation request is provided in Section 20003 (Missile Defense) of the Reconciliation Exhibit.

       The FY 2026 request was reduced by $1.798 million for Advisory and Assistance Services to promote efficiencies and advance the policies of the Administration
       in alignment with Executive Order 14222, "Implementing the President's Department of Government Efficiency Cost Efficiency Initiative."

       The FY 2026 request was reduced by $0.485 million for civilian personnel to optimize the workforce in compliance with Executive Order 14210, "Implementing the
       President's Department of Government Efficiency Workforce Optimization Initiative."

       FY24: Decrease of $3.132M is SBIR/STTR/FTT Assessment (SBIR).

       FY26: Decrease of $.194M is for program adjustments.




