       Change Summary Explanation
       "The FY 2026 request was reduced by $0.005 million for Advisory and Assistance Services to promote efficiencies and advance the policies of the Administration
       in alignment with Executive Order 14222, "Implementing the President's Department of Government Efficiency Cost Efficiency Initiative."

       The FY 2026 request was reduced by $1.077 million for civilian personnel to optimize the workforce in compliance with Executive Order 14210, "Implementing the
       President's Department of Government Efficiency Workforce Optimization Initiative."

       The FY 2026 increase includes support SLQ-25E countermeasures capability improvements, and support for development of an anti-torpedo torpedo defense
       hard kill capability. Decreases include misc rate adjustments and efficiencies.

       Countermeasure Anti-Torpedo Torpedo (CAT) sustainment ended in FY 2024 with the turnover of all CAT material to the Navy's CRAW program. Shipyard
       schedules shifted in FY 2025 to extend the life of CVN-68 until FY 2028. Sustainment of both CVN-68 and CVN-77 is now required to allow for a ready for use
       Torpedo Warning System (TWS) through FY 2028 for CVN-68 and FY 2030 on CVN-77. The new torpedo defense hard kill program starts in FY 2026 with the
       development of a single tow threat torpedo detection array in line with an acoustic countermeasure device. The Hard kill Program will use the MK-58 torpedo as
       the hard kill weapon once that torpedo is fully developed. Through integration and testing the Hard Kill Program will be developed through FY 2030. The US Navy
       plans to install this torpedo hard-kill countermeasure on over 165 different surface ships.




