Sensor, Pilotage and Targeting Systems, VMS/Flight Control, Software/Hardware architectures, Crewed/
Uncrewed Teaming, and other related follow on activities. Support for these efforts will come from Government,
industry and academia such as Naval Research Labs, DARPA, Georgia Tech Research Institute, John Hopkins
APL, Penn State University Applied Research Lab, RAND Corp, and various industry partners. Final production
of MS-A supporting documents may include but are not limited to: an Acquisition Strategy (AS), Capabilities
Development Document (CDD), Developmental CONOPs, Life Cycle Cost Estimate (LCCE), Life Cycle
Sustainment Plan (LCSP) and Systems Engineering Plan (SEP).
FY 2027 Base Plans:
Continuation of pre-Milestone A activities to include analysis, studies, and production of acquisition
documentation. MS-A supporting documents may include but are not limited to: an Acquisition Strategy (AS),
Capabilities Development Document (CDD), Developmental CONOPs, Life Cycle Cost Estimate (LCCE), Life
Cycle Sustainment Plan (LCSP) and Systems Engineering Plan (SEP). The FVL (MS) program will support
MOSA objective architecture efforts.
