D. Acquisition Strategy
The Navy awarded a sole source contract to Kongsberg Defense & Aerospace (KDA), the manufacturer of the NSM, initiating production in FY 2024. This contract
encompasses engineering services focused on system improvements. Starting in FY 2025, the Marine Corps has actively utilized these engineering services,
supplemented by design and test support from government laboratories. Starting in FY 2027, the program will leverage the Department of War Strike Missile Advanced
Research and Technology (SMART) Project Agreement with the Ministry of Defence of the Kingdom of Norway. As sub-systems reach maturity, they will be integrated
into the NSM production baseline, enabling standardized production for both the Navy and Marine Corps.




