D. Acquisition Strategy
The Navy competitively awarded two Cost Plus Fixed Fee Technical Development phase contracts to develop the Advanced Arresting Gear (AAG) system. Upon
completion of the Preliminary Design and Integrated Baseline reviews, the Navy awarded a single Cost Plus Award Fee option to General Atomics for the System
Development and Demonstration (SDD) phase to develop and demonstrate a production representative AAG at the NAVAIR Lakehurst Jet Car Track Site and Runway
Arrested Landing Site. AAG has transitioned from the design and development phase into concurrent production and sustainment phase.




